On Mon, 6 Sep 1999, Rogier Wolff wrote:
> There is no kernel-wide max-fd limit. ??? <- Someone correct me on this.
>                                              I'm not sure....
/proc/sys/fs/file-max is the system-wide fd descriptor limit. Currently
this can be upped to over 1 million.
